item.title: Rs2 Deobfuscator
item.dc:creator: @qauters qauters
item.description:
@qauters wrote:

the bank:

Actually, it is very easy to rename a client to the exact way it was. When you deob, since it is ZKM, it generates a “deob log”. Have a java reader parse this log, and you can rename everything back to the way it was very fast and effectively.

Actually, that’s the rename part, not the complete deobfuscation. It set’s all access flags to public. It removes flow obfuscation etc. You can’t just add that back again.
Never forget that only renaming isn’t deobfuscating.

Read full topic
